prompt:
Add a public async function called ProcessAsync to AsyncOps.calr that calls another async method and awaits the result. It takes no parameters and returns Task<i32>.

Use this exact Calor await syntax:
§AF{f001:ProcessAsync:pub}
  §O{Task<i32>}
  §E{net:r}
  §B{data} §AWAIT §C{FetchDataAsync}§/C
  §R (* data 2)
§/AF{f001}

The §AWAIT expr syntax awaits an async expression:
- §AWAIT goes before the async call
- The result is unwrapped from the Task
- Must be used inside an async function (§AF)
